text: Have you guys noticed the high number of cards with art with extreme forced perspective in this block?
Accursed Horde, Supreme Will, that blue steal spell from Amonkhet...
I think it's kinda necessary to show off the size and power of the gods, right?
Yeah, it's kinda cool. We didn't get this stuff on Theros or Zendikar, really

I've liked it. Supreme Will is a great piece of art.
Does Bontu's Last Reckoning use forced perspective?
Not exactly. Not in the same way that Accursed Horde does
Accursed Horde gives you a kind of 3D effect.
That said, the art on Bontu's Last Reckoning does a good job of showing her size, and is some lovely art.
Gotcha. I think I have more of an idea of what forced perspective is now.
More extreme perspective: Deem Worthy, Faith of the Devoted, Gideon's Intervention, Glorious End, Lay Claim, Nest of Scarabs, Shadow of the Grave
Do the three gods use it? Or are they more so just use "scale birds"?
More scale birds, but the Locust God has a little extra going for him with the mummies up close in the foreground, and far in the back.
What about the Scarab and the legion of Eternals?
But nothing about him is distorted to show his size. If one of his hands was huge and reaching towards you, that would be extreme.
Oh ok.
Which card is that?
Oh, The Scarab God.
Oh, I see.
Yeah, not quite so much
Are you big into MTG art or is thatbjust something you noticed for this set?
